 \lim_{\epsilon \to 0_+} \frac{1}{\pi}\int_{-\frac{R}{\epsilon}}^{\frac{R}{\epsilon}}\frac{\sin(z)}{z}(\varphi(\epsilon z)-\varphi(0)) = 0
s=t\varepsilon
u=-s
\frac{\varphi(t)-\varphi(-t)}t=\int_{-1}^1\varphi'(tu)du
\lim_{\varepsilon\to 0}\int_0^R\frac{\varphi(t)-\varphi(-t)}t\cdot \sin\left(\frac t\varepsilon\right)dt=0.
